root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2725</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:addr>axt-000N</fr:addr><fr:route>axt-000N.xml</fr:route><fr:source-path>/Users/ayberkt/Code/mathematical-forest/trees/public/axt-000N.tree</fr:source-path><fr:title>The point functor</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>7</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author>Samson Abramsky</fr:author><fr:author>Achim Jung</fr:author></fr:authors><fr:last-changed><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>9</fr:day></fr:date></fr:last-changed></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>
  Let <fr:tex>L</fr:tex> be a frame.
  A <fr:em>point</fr:em> of <fr:tex>L</fr:tex> is a <fr:em>completely prime filter</fr:em> of the lattice <fr:tex>L</fr:tex>.
</fr:p><fr:p>
  The collection of all points of a frame <fr:tex>L</fr:tex> is denoted <fr:tex>\mathsf {pt} ( L )</fr:tex>.
</fr:p><fr:p>
  This collection of all points can be topologised by equipping it with a class
  of opens as follows.
</fr:p><fr:p>
  Let <fr:tex>U  \subseteq   \mathsf {pt} ( L )</fr:tex> be a set of points of <fr:tex>L</fr:tex>. The set <fr:tex>U</fr:tex> is
  taken as open if it satisfies: <fr:tex
display="block">\exists  x  \in  L. \  \forall  F  \in  U. \  x  \in    F.</fr:tex> In other words, there is some "open" <fr:tex>x  \in  L</fr:tex> which is an open
  neighbourhood of every "point" <fr:tex>F  \in  U.</fr:tex></fr:p><fr:p>
  This can be viewed as a mapping <fr:tex>\mathsf {pt}  :  \mathbf {Frm}   \to   \mathbf {Top}</fr:tex>, which is then extended
  to a contravariant functor <fr:tex>\mathbf {Frm} ^{ \mathsf {op}}  \to   \mathbf {Top}</fr:tex>. Let
  <fr:tex>h : M  \to  L</fr:tex> be a frame homomorphism. The functor <fr:tex>\mathsf {pt}</fr:tex> should then give
  a continuous map <fr:tex>\mathsf {pt} (h) :  \mathsf {pt} ( L )   \to   \mathsf {pt} ( M )</fr:tex> which is defined as
  <fr:tex
display="block">\mathsf {pt} (h)(F) := h^{-1}(F).</fr:tex></fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:related><fr:backlinks></fr:backlinks><fr:references></fr:references></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>